16
00:01:34,770 --> 00:01:36,680
Okay. It's like this.

17
00:01:36,680 --> 00:01:40,000
Since everyone is here, let's do a small meeting.

18
00:01:40,000 --> 00:01:42,080
Everyone is busy. I'll keep the long story short.

19
00:01:42,080 --> 00:01:46,340
The wife of the Chairman of Hua Man Real Estate has breast cancer relapse again.

20
00:01:46,340 --> 00:01:49,560
There are no obvious effects after treatment in other hospitals.

21
00:01:49,560 --> 00:01:52,700
She wants to be transferred to our hospital to continue treatment.

22
00:01:52,700 --> 00:01:55,320
The wife of the Chairman of Hua Man Real Estate?

23
00:01:55,320 --> 00:01:58,830
- Don't tell me you're talking about Ge Xue Hong? 
 - Ge Xue Hong?

24
00:01:58,830 --> 00:02:01,050
How can someone have this kind of name?

25
00:02:01,050 --> 00:02:03,250
She has relapse of breast cancer?

26
00:02:03,250 --> 00:02:07,150
Why don't she go to the breast surgery department or oncology department? Why does she want to come to our emergency department?

27
00:02:07,150 --> 00:02:09,080
It's like this. No matter what reason they have,

28
00:02:09,080 --> 00:02:11,860
since they trust our hospital,

29
00:02:11,860 --> 00:02:15,090
we must live up to their trust, right?

30
00:02:15,090 --> 00:02:17,400
and Dean Jiang also specially told me

31
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:19,220
that we must show

32
00:02:19,220 --> 00:02:21,440
our Tongshan Hospital's enthusiasm.

33
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:23,490
Enthusiasm?

34
00:02:23,490 --> 00:02:26,620
- What kind of enthusiasm? 
 I know.

35
00:02:26,620 --> 00:02:28,530
I heard from the people of the infrastructure department

36
00:02:28,530 --> 00:02:32,640
that someone is planning to donate a new laboratory building.

37
00:02:32,640 --> 00:02:35,720
Don't tell me the person is Ge Xue Hong?

38
00:02:35,720 --> 00:02:39,080
She already paid of it. Of course we need to serve her well.

39
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:41,790
What serve?

40
00:02:41,790 --> 00:02:44,320
We should be more enthusiastic to our patients, shouldn't we?

41
00:02:44,320 --> 00:02:49,410
Besides, she donated a building to us. She is also supporting our healthcare.

42
00:02:49,410 --> 00:02:52,400
We should respond with our enthusiasm.

43
00:02:52,400 --> 00:02:54,490
Sounds really impressive.

44
00:02:54,490 --> 00:02:57,480
Let's put this aside. There's an important point.

45
00:02:57,480 --> 00:03:02,290
This patient has a request for her attending physician's 
seniority.

46
00:03:02,290 --> 00:03:06,140
So I and Dean Jiang have carefully discussed about it.

47
00:03:06,140 --> 00:03:11,270
We have planned for Doctor Xiao to accept this Ge Xue Hong...

48
00:03:11,270 --> 00:03:13,210
The Ge Hong patient.

49
00:03:13,210 --> 00:03:15,110
You have no opinions, right?

50
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:24,840
You guys were chatting well and suddenly talked about me.

51
00:03:24,840 --> 00:03:29,920
Director, I have a lot of patients on hand now.

52
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:33,840
How about letting Tang Hua look after your patients?

53
00:03:33,840 --> 00:03:36,350
Director, I think

54
00:03:36,350 --> 00:03:39,530
you know the function of our ER and EICU more than me.

55
00:03:39,530 --> 00:03:42,810
- Xiao Yan... 
 - Director, I also heard you guys chatting just now.

56
00:03:42,810 --> 00:03:45,680
Donating building and such. We understand

57
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:47,440
that your work has difficulties, too.

58
00:03:47,440 --> 00:03:51,330
But I can't accept this patient.

59
00:03:51,330 --> 00:03:54,190
I go and make my rounds first. You guys chat.

60
00:03:58,300 --> 00:04:01,950
- Director, I... 
 - Since Xiao Yan is busy,

61
00:04:01,950 --> 00:04:03,690
then

62
00:04:04,520 --> 00:04:06,400
how about you accept, Yi Ran?

63
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:08,690
Me?

64
00:04:08,690 --> 00:04:11,800
Director, I reckon Ge Xue Hong won't want me due to my seniority.

65
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:14,660
- You choose somebody else instead. 
 - I'll do it.

66
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:21,020
- You? 
 - Why?

67
00:04:21,020 --> 00:04:23,030
My seniority is not enough?

68
00:04:24,460 --> 00:04:27,500
- Your seniority is enough. It's just... 
 - Then forget it.

69
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:29,650
Then you ask Doctor Tang Hua

70
00:04:29,650 --> 00:04:31,450
or Chen Zhi.

71
00:04:31,450 --> 00:04:34,820
- Okay. 
 - At most, this laboratory building will not be built.

72
00:04:34,820 --> 00:04:37,450
Anyway, Dean won't do anything to you.

73
00:04:37,450 --> 00:04:40,490
Director, since someone volunteered, you just let him do it.

74
00:04:40,490 --> 00:04:42,720
Anyway, if there are any problems later, there's someone to take the blame, isn't it?

75
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:46,480
Take what blame? If there's a need for someone to take the blame, I'm the one.

76
00:04:48,980 --> 00:04:52,320
Since Bai Zhu volunteered,

77
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:55,320
then you accept this patient.

78
00:04:55,320 --> 00:04:58,260
There's something I need to remind you. Because I heard this patient

79
00:04:58,260 --> 00:05:00,630
has a long-term illness, her temper is not good.

80
00:05:00,630 --> 00:05:05,620
- And she's quite mean. 
 - This aspect is similar to Bai Zhu.

81
00:05:05,620 --> 00:05:07,130
Don't create trouble.

82
00:05:07,130 --> 00:05:09,110
Bai Zhu, I must remind you.

83
00:05:09,110 --> 00:05:11,750
- You must manage your emotions well. 
 - Don't worry.

84
00:05:11,750 --> 00:05:14,650
I'll take the blame if any problems arise.

85
00:05:14,650 --> 00:05:16,290
Okay.

86
00:05:16,290 --> 00:05:19,660
Since Doctor Bai is the attending physician,

87
00:05:19,660 --> 00:05:21,890
we must cooperate with him well.

88
00:05:21,890 --> 00:05:23,700
We try our best to make the patient satisfied,

89
00:05:23,700 --> 00:05:25,480
including Nurse Jiang,

90
00:05:25,480 --> 00:05:28,650
- your side... 
 - Don't worry about the nursing side. I will personally look after.

91
00:05:28,650 --> 00:05:31,250
Don't worry, We'll serve

92
00:05:31,250 --> 00:05:34,100
Ge Xue Hong, this living "Buddha", well.

93
00:05:35,130 --> 00:05:37,750
Okay. Then we'll go with this first. We carry on with our work.

94
00:05:37,750 --> 00:05:40,750
Xiao Bai, I have something to tell you. I must...

95
00:05:42,800 --> 00:05:45,800
It's okay. Even though Doctor Bai said it like that,

96
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:48,400
he actually has a good sense of responsibility.

97
00:05:48,400 --> 00:05:50,800
As long as there are no problems.

98
00:05:52,120 --> 00:05:58,040
<i>[Emergency]</i>

99
00:05:58,040 --> 00:06:00,360
- Remove? 
 - That's right.

100
00:06:00,360 --> 00:06:02,390
Both breasts need to be removed.

101
00:06:02,390 --> 00:06:05,270
Only this way, the lesions can be completely removed.

102
00:06:05,270 --> 00:06:08,920
Otherwise, it's incurable if the cancer cells spread.

103
00:06:10,820 --> 00:06:14,220
Don't you specialize in creating miracles?

104
00:06:14,900 --> 00:06:17,850
You misunderstood. I'm not the one doing the surgery for you.

105
00:06:17,850 --> 00:06:20,960
But I can tell you, after the surgery,

106
00:06:20,960 --> 00:06:24,810
it's already biggest miracle when the cancer cells don't spread anymore.

107
00:06:27,570 --> 00:06:29,330
I'm not removing.

108
00:06:30,150 --> 00:06:32,080
Remove or die. You choose.

109
00:06:32,080 --> 00:06:34,280
I'm not removing!

110
00:06:36,630 --> 00:06:38,680
I cannot die, too.

111
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:44,280
It's okay. You still have time to consider.

112
00:06:44,280 --> 00:06:47,610
When you've thought it through, come and find me again.

113
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:56,930
Come in.

114
00:06:56,930 --> 00:06:58,940
Teacher, you're looking for me?

115
00:06:58,940 --> 00:07:01,570
How's the matter on Ge Hong's surgery?

116
00:07:01,570 --> 00:07:03,950
She still doesn't want to do the resection surgery.

117
00:07:03,950 --> 00:07:07,080
It's very difficult to make up the mind.

118
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:09,350
But we cannot delay her condition any longer.

119
00:07:09,350 --> 00:07:11,800
- You have to convince her as soon as possible. 
 - How can I convince her?

120
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:13,680
Think of a way!

121
00:07:13,680 --> 00:07:15,850
You are her attending physician.

122
00:07:15,850 --> 00:07:18,160
- You are the dean. 
 - How are you talking to me?

123
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:21,880
Teacher, there's really nothing I can do. Really.

124
00:07:25,180 --> 00:07:28,910
Teacher, if you can transfer me back to Cardiac Surgery,

125
00:07:28,910 --> 00:07:31,610
maybe I will be struck by a brainwave and think of a very good idea.

126
00:07:31,610 --> 00:07:33,200
Get lost.

127
00:07:41,710 --> 00:07:43,730
Close the door.

128
00:07:49,200 --> 00:07:52,440
That thought of yours, Dean won't see it?

129
00:07:52,440 --> 00:07:56,340
Based on your usual virtues, you will accept a patient like Ge Hong?

130
00:07:56,340 --> 00:07:59,380
When something is unusual, there must be a bad reason for it. Dean rejected you, right?

131
00:07:59,380 --> 00:08:01,280
He told me to get lost.

132
00:08:01,280 --> 00:08:03,640
That's right.

133
00:08:03,640 --> 00:08:08,480
Is there any way to make Ge Hong change her mind?

134
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:12,810
Then you have think why she doesn't want to remove first. What is the secret behind it.

135
00:08:12,810 --> 00:08:14,990
I found this.

136
00:08:19,480 --> 00:08:21,040
When she was young?

137
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:23,390
When she was young, she was gorgeous woman. She was good-looking her whole life.

138
00:08:23,390 --> 00:08:25,760
She cares about her looks and figure the most.

139
00:08:25,760 --> 00:08:30,390
So she's almost 50 years old now but looks like she just turned 40.

140
00:08:31,530 --> 00:08:33,590
Being good-looking or saving her life is more important?

141
00:08:33,590 --> 00:08:36,440
She can't even understand this. She lived 50 years for nothing.

142
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:41,220
But don't forget, she's currently fighting with a young pretty woman for her husband.

143
00:08:41,220 --> 00:08:44,680
To Ge Hong, she's disadvantaged on this matter.

144
00:08:44,680 --> 00:08:47,260
If she removes both her breasts,

145
00:08:47,260 --> 00:08:49,230
isn't it equivalent of her surrendering?

146
00:08:49,230 --> 00:08:53,300
She was hospitalized for so long. Did her husband come to see her once?

147
00:08:53,300 --> 00:08:55,080
Giving up her life for a man like this,

148
00:08:55,080 --> 00:08:56,810
she's really stupid.

149
00:08:56,810 --> 00:08:58,560
You're a bit like Tang Hua.

150
00:08:58,560 --> 00:09:03,670
No matter man or woman, sacrificing oneself for unworthy people, that's stupid.

151
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:08,960
Xiao Yan, discussing patients' privacy is not your style.

152
00:09:08,960 --> 00:09:14,000
Are you caring about the patient or helping our Teacher Bai?

153
00:09:18,710 --> 00:09:22,590
Do you know that Ge Hong has a daughter studying in Britain now?

154
00:09:22,590 --> 00:09:26,810
If you can't convince her, you can consider asking her daughter to convince her.

155
00:09:26,810 --> 00:09:29,020
I found her daughter's email address.

156
00:09:29,020 --> 00:09:32,010
Why not you try to send an email to her?

157
00:09:40,730 --> 00:09:45,010
- Is it okay if I write like this? 
 - How about adding one more line, "Hope that you come back to the country,

158
00:09:45,010 --> 00:09:47,680
your mother needs someone to take care of her".

159
00:09:53,440 --> 00:09:55,680
Okay. You can send it.

160
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:04,020
Xian Yun?

161
00:10:06,310 --> 00:10:11,020
Don't move, don't move. Are you ok?

162
00:10:11,020 --> 00:10:14,100
I'm fine. I just hate myself for being so useless.

163
00:10:14,100 --> 00:10:18,650
Hate me for coming home late. It's past dinner.

164
00:10:18,650 --> 00:10:21,310
Take your time, don't hurt yourself.

165
00:10:21,310 --> 00:10:25,550
Here, let me push you out before I clear up.

166
00:10:25,550 --> 00:10:27,990
You didn't burn yourself right?

167
00:10:38,050 --> 00:10:42,500
I've cleared it all up. Now I'll make dinner.

168
00:10:44,010 --> 00:10:49,280
Here. In future don't get restless. Just wait for me.

169
00:10:52,080 --> 00:10:55,030
Do you have a cold? Don't give it to me.

170
00:10:55,030 --> 00:10:56,130
No, it's just a runny nose.

171
00:10:56,130 --> 00:10:59,080
Come here, I have some medicine. Let me make it up for you.

172
00:10:59,080 --> 00:11:02,560
I'll do it, I'll do it.

173
00:11:18,920 --> 00:11:23,680
Why don't we hire a nurse?

174
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:27,270
Why are you bringing that up again?

175
00:11:27,270 --> 00:11:30,440
I know I'm too proud. I really hate myself for it.

176
00:11:30,440 --> 00:11:33,910
I wanted to prove that I could take care of myself, but look what happened.

177
00:11:33,910 --> 00:11:35,640
You had to spend all that time clearing up.

178
00:11:35,640 --> 00:11:39,690
I'm your wife, if I don't clear up, who will?

179
00:11:40,770 --> 00:11:43,290
Let's hire a nurse, ok?

180
00:11:43,290 --> 00:11:46,520
Then you can stop worrying about me at work.

181
00:11:46,520 --> 00:11:49,460
Why don't you call that male nurse,

182
00:11:49,460 --> 00:11:53,720
ask him if he found a job or not. Hey, take your time.

183
00:11:55,230 --> 00:11:57,690
Just ask him.

184
00:11:57,690 --> 00:12:01,610
It's hard to find home nurses these days. And his rates were so cheap he's definitely been snapped up.

185
00:12:01,610 --> 00:12:05,270
Don't worry, leave it to me.

186
00:12:05,270 --> 00:12:08,080
I'll ask him. Now I'll make dinner.

187
00:12:34,180 --> 00:12:37,530
<i>[Director Chen]<i></i></i>

188
00:12:47,190 --> 00:12:48,170
<i>[Nurses Station]<i></i></i>

189
00:12:48,170 --> 00:12:50,320
Lin Zhi. Remove the IV on bed 4.

190
00:12:50,320 --> 00:12:51,910
Alright.

191
00:12:51,910 --> 00:12:54,890
Monitoring Room No. 2 needs temperature taken every hour.

192
00:12:59,010 --> 00:13:00,360
Head Nurse.

193
00:13:00,360 --> 00:13:03,000
- Director. 
 - You see, I asked Fan.

194
00:13:03,000 --> 00:13:05,250
He hasn't found anything more suitable yet,

195
00:13:05,250 --> 00:13:08,190
so he's able to work for you. I'm so happy to hear it.

196
00:13:08,190 --> 00:13:11,310
I didn't tell you, how did you know?

197
00:13:11,310 --> 00:13:14,760
Last night, Xian Yun sent me a message.

198
00:13:14,760 --> 00:13:17,370
He was worried you wouldn't know how to tell me.

199
00:13:18,710 --> 00:13:23,220
Director, I've given you so much trouble. Looking and then not looking.

200
00:13:23,220 --> 00:13:25,050
Of course not!

201
00:13:25,050 --> 00:13:28,410
How about I give Fan a call and ask him to come here this afternoon.

202
00:13:28,410 --> 00:13:32,410
You two can discuss things in person, and he can go back with you to get used to the house.

203
00:13:32,410 --> 00:13:34,460
You can decide when he starts.

204
00:13:34,460 --> 00:13:36,060
Ok.

205
00:13:36,060 --> 00:13:40,320
Director, I'm sorry for being so much trouble.

206
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:43,450
Don't be so modest.

207
00:13:43,450 --> 00:13:46,170
Once things settle down at home, I can give you extra jobs!

208
00:13:46,170 --> 00:13:48,560
I promise I will work hard.

209
00:13:48,560 --> 00:13:51,430
Oh yes, how is Ge Hong doing?

210
00:13:51,430 --> 00:13:55,940
She seems to be doing well. This morning Doctor Bai brought in an oncology doctor to see her.

211
00:13:55,940 --> 00:13:59,150
- I see. Well, I won't keep you any longer. 
 - Yes.

212
00:14:02,590 --> 00:14:06,180
Director! Thank you.

213
00:14:09,570 --> 00:14:12,750
Director Chen, why are you so happy?

214
00:14:13,680 --> 00:14:15,510
Get back to work.

215
00:14:20,490 --> 00:14:22,560
Thank you, Doctor.

216
00:14:30,910 --> 00:14:32,850
Doctor Bai, do you remember me?

217
00:14:32,850 --> 00:14:36,860
You're back from Beijing. Are you in a rush this time as well?

218
00:14:36,860 --> 00:14:39,030
You-you still remember me.

219
00:14:39,030 --> 00:14:40,040
Is it still the high blood pressure?

220
00:14:40,040 --> 00:14:41,650
These last two days, I haven't been well.

221
00:14:41,650 --> 00:14:43,700
I remember what you told me about last time Doctor Bai,

222
00:14:43,700 --> 00:14:46,580
so I went to get a CT done at San Hospital.

223
00:14:46,580 --> 00:14:47,700
Let me have a look.

224
00:14:47,700 --> 00:14:49,180
Here it is.

225
00:14:59,860 --> 00:15:01,310
Do you have the endocrinology report?

226
00:15:01,310 --> 00:15:03,260
Here.

227
00:15:09,470 --> 00:15:14,070
Looking at the results, you seem to have an adrenal tumor. It's benign.

228
00:15:14,070 --> 00:15:17,770
This has caused your high blood pressure.

229
00:15:17,770 --> 00:15:20,210
The doctors at San Hospital said the same thing.

230
00:15:20,210 --> 00:15:23,270
Why didn't get treated at San Hospital then?

231
00:15:23,270 --> 00:15:26,430
Doctor Bai, you still have a grudge?

232
00:15:27,300 --> 00:15:28,840
So about my tumor...

233
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:31,300
Since it's benign, we'll do a surgery to remove it.

234
00:15:31,300 --> 00:15:34,100
It should help with the high blood pressure as well.

235
00:15:34,100 --> 00:15:36,040
Really? Thank you, Doctor Bai.

236
00:15:36,040 --> 00:15:38,460
My high blood pressure

237
00:15:38,460 --> 00:15:40,100
has been a problem for so many years.

238
00:15:40,100 --> 00:15:41,710
Go and complete the hospitalization procedures.

239
00:15:41,710 --> 00:15:44,800
I'll schedule your surgery as soon as possible.

240
00:15:44,800 --> 00:15:46,920
Thank you, thank you.

241
00:15:48,130 --> 00:15:51,060
Doctor Bai, you are the cleverest,

242
00:15:51,060 --> 00:15:53,410
most responsible doctor I've met!

243
00:15:54,540 --> 00:15:57,950
As well as the doctor with the sharpest tongue.

244
00:16:18,730 --> 00:16:20,340
Hello.

